{{italictitle}}
'''''Hortus Cantabrigiensis''''' is a catalogue of plants grown in the [[Cambridge Botanic Garden|Walkerian Botanic Garden]], a forerunner of the present Botanic Garden of [[Cambridge University]], originally compiled by its first curator [[James Donn]] and published in 1796. A further 12 editions were published, the last in 1845, long after Donn's death.<ref name=Donn>[https://archive.org/details/hortuscantabrig00gardgoog Donn, J. (1809). ''Hortus Cantabrigiensis'']</ref>

